<p><b>Sarah Ann McLachlan</b>, <a href="/wiki/Order_of_Canada" title="Order of Canada">OC</a>, <a href="/wiki/Order_of_British_Columbia" title="Order of British Columbia">OBC</a> (born January 28, 1968<span style="display:none">(<span class="bday">1968-01-28</span>)</span>) is a <a href="/wiki/Canada" title="Canada">Canadian</a> <a href="/wiki/Musician" title="Musician">musician</a>, singer and <a href="/wiki/Songwriter" title="Songwriter">songwriter</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-gg_2-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-gg-2" title=""><span>[</span>3<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<p>She is known for the emotional sound of her ballads and <a href="/wiki/Mezzo-soprano" title="Mezzo-soprano">mezzo-soprano</a> vocal range.<sup id="cite_ref-3" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-3" title=""><span>[</span>4<span>]</span></a></sup> As of 2006, she has sold over 40 million albums worldwide. Her best-selling album to date is <i><a href="/wiki/Surfacing_(album)" title="Surfacing (album)">Surfacing</a></i>, for which she won two <a href="/wiki/Grammy_Award" title="Grammy Award">Grammy Awards</a> (out of three nominations) and eight <a href="/wiki/Juno_Award" title="Juno Award">Juno Awards</a>. In addition to her personal artistic efforts, she founded the <a href="/wiki/Lilith_Fair" title="Lilith Fair">Lilith Fair</a> tour, which showcased female musicians in the late 1990s.</p>
